SIMPLE: headdress
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Headdress
<hw>Head"dress`</hw> <pr>(h⟦ecr⟧d"dr⟦ecr⟧s`)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>A covering or ornament for the head; a headtire;
<as>as, chiefs among the plains Indians had elaborate long
<ex>headdresses</ex> with many feathers</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Among birds the males very often appear in a most beautiful
<qex>headdress</qex>, whether it be a crest, a comb, a tuft of feathers,
or a natural little plume.</q> <rj><qau>Addison.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A manner of dressing the hair or of adorning it,
whether with or without a veil, ribbons, combs, etc.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Headed</ent>⟦br⟧
